article.headline: UNLV 68, San Diego St. 58
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Wink Adams scored a game-high 23 points to lead UNLV over San Diego State 68-58 Tuesday in a Mountain West Conference game. Joe Darger scored 13 points and Rene Rougeau added 10 points, nine rebounds, and three steals for the Rebels (21-6, 10-3). UNLV remained in second place in the conference after first place BYU defeated New Mexico 70-69 in overtime Tuesday night. Lorrenzo Wade led the Aztecs (18-10, 8-6) with 19 points and nine rebounds. Billy White added nine points and six rebounds for San Diego State, which remains in fourth place in the Mountain West. After trailing 33-31 at halftime, the Rebels opened the second half on a 13-3 run and never trailed again. UNLV built its largest lead of the game 62-51 with 4:22 left. The Aztecs built their largest lead at 14-6 with 12:28 left in the session. Adams eventually rallied the Rebels, scoring eight consecutive points, giving the Rebels a 24-23 lead with 5:11 until halftime.
